        <h1>About me</h1>
        <p>Hello ! My name is Congming Gao, and I'm currently a Ph.D student in Computer Science at the <a href="http://english.cqu.edu.cn/">Chongqing University </a>, China. <br>
          <br>
          My research interests gravitate toward Computer Architecture, Emerging Non-Volatile Memory, Flash Memory, and Embedded and Real-Time Systems. I'm also curious about all mathematics and sciences in general. 
          <br>
          <br>
          In 2014, I obtained a Bachelor Degree in Computer Science at CQU with great honours. <br>
In 2014.09,         I stayed at the same school  to complete a Ph.D under the supervision of <a href="https://faculty.ecnu.edu.cn/s/3969/t/39253/main.jspy">Dr. Shi </a>, <a href="http://www.bdsc.site/team-page/193.html">Dr. Liu </a> and <a href="https://faculty.ecnu.edu.cn/s/3741/main.jspy">Dr. Edwin Sha </a> to complete my education. <br>
Now, I'm a Visiting Scholar with the  Department  of  Electrical  andComputer Engineering, University of Pittsburgh under the supervision of <a href="https://www.engineering.pitt.edu/jun_yang/">Dr. Yang </a> and <a href="http://people.cs.pitt.edu/~zhangyt/">Dr. Zhang </a>. <br>
        </p>
